The body of a missing woman was found inside an abandoned Cleveland home. Anastasia Hamilton, 25, was discovered dead on a couch inside the vacant house in the city’s Slavic Village district Wednesday, according to WEWS-TV. Hamilton’s body was riddled with lacerations and abrasions to the head and torso, police reportedly said. The apparent murder victim was last seen on Saturday night with an unknown man on security footage from the parking lot of the Terminal Tower residential skyscraper, according to the article. Her body was located by police after they received a tip from a witness, the outlet said. Cops were reportedly offering $5,000 for information that led to an arrest.